;   *<br>> <br>> Aadyaa (Kaali) represents the state of sha=
kti just after Shiva and <br>> Shakti separated and the field of duality=
 is just about to spring from <br>> non-dual Self. This primordial energ=
y is fierce, intense, disorderly and <br>> uncontrolled and that is seen=

 in a lot of symbols associated with Kaali.<br>> <br>> When this pri=
mordial energy decides to give rise to the field of duality <br>> and Cr=
eation, it becomes Taaraa. Though very similar to Kaali (one <br>> Tantr=
a even says, with a bit of hyperbole, that Kaali and Taaraa are the <br>>=
; same and one distinguishing between them will go to hell!), She has an <b=
r>> added compassion and Motherly aspect.<br>> <br>> When this sha=
kti becomes more orderly and masterfully contemplates the <br>> masterpl=
an for the way entire duality should operate, it becomes Shodasi <br>> (=
Lalita Tripurasundari).<br>> <br>> When this shakti plans how various=
 worlds (realms of awareness) operate <br>> and interact within this dua=
lity, it becomes Bhuvaneswari.<br>> <br>> When this shakti contemplat=
es how the field of duality to be created <br>> would recycle itself and=
 keep going continuously (i.e. how objects are <br>> destroyed and
 then=
 re-created), it becomes Bhairavi.<br>> <br>> When this shakti contem=
plates how Self would manifest as various objects <br>> in the field of =
duality and engage in give and take to make the field of <br>> duality s=
ustainable and self-sufficient, and, at the same time, make <br>> each o=
bject in the field of duality a microcosm of the *entire* field, <br>> w=
ith that fact concealed by a false identity in each object, it becomes <br>=
> Vajra Vairochani (Chhinnamasta).<br>> <br>> When this shakti con=
templates how to make the objects in the field of <br>> duality immerse =
themselves in duality with awareness of underlying <br>> non-dual Self c=
ompletely masked off, it becomes Dhoomavati. (Note: So <br>> she is also=
 the key to reversing it). That's why she is a widow and some <br>> stor=
ies describe her as eating her own Shiva.<br>> <br>> When this shakti=
 contemplates how the field of duality would restrain <br>>
 beings from=
 escaping it (e.g. various internal enemies and pashas), it <br>> become=
s Valga. With some corruption, the Vedic name Valga (meaning: <br>> brid=
le or rein!) became Bagla. Of course, she is the key to <br>> understand=
ing and overcoming those restraints that keep us tied in <br>> duality.<=
br>> <br>> When this shakti contemplates how the field of duality wou=
ld mesmerize <br>> beings with its variety and keep them trapped in it d=
ue to the curiosity <br>> to understand more of it, it becomes Maatangi.=
<br>> <br>> When this shakti contemplates how to keep the beings happ=
y and fulfilled <br>> and keep them engaged in the field of duality, it =
then becomes Kamala.<br>> <br>> *      =
